defaultCambridgeshire is a diverse county, consisting of large rural areas, market towns and the city of 
defaultCambridge
default.
default The issues facing rural areas vary considerably across the county. In Fenland, in the north of the county, the key concerns are linked to an ageing
default population, deprivation, educational attainment and health inequalities, while in rural areas to the south of the county the overriding issue is the availability of transport to access services. Improving transport has an important role to play in reducin
defaultg social exclusion, improving accessibility and helping people to live independent lives, but the location of services and choices as to how they are provided often have significant transport impacts. 
defaultDifferent groups in the county face a variety of transp
defaultort problems, for example children and young people often rely on parents to provide transport where public transport opportunities do not exist
